Taranis Q X7 + FrSky XSR-SIM – Robot Control Setup (Current State)
Hardware
Radio: FrSky Taranis Q X7
Simulator dongle: FrSky XSR-SIM (USB joystick)
Q X7 – ROBOT Model Configuration
Model
Dedicated model name: ROBOT
Used for: ground robot teleop via XSR-SIM
Inputs
I1: STR → Source: Rud (left stick, left/right) – steering
I2: FWD → Source: Thr (left stick, up/down) – forward/back
I3: AU1 → Source: Ele (right stick, up/down) – auxiliary 1
I4: AU2 → Source: Ail (right stick, left/right) – auxiliary 2
(All inputs assumed linear: no expo, no curves, weight = 100.)
Mixes → Channels
CH1 ← I1: STR → steering / angular velocity (ω)
CH2 ← I2: FWD → forward/back / linear velocity (v)
CH3 ← I3: AU1 → spare (AUX1)
CH4 ← I4: AU2 → spare (AUX2)